 the same type are collected into batches and stored for later input to the computer. Processing proceeds in discrete runs, making it easier to control as data can be checked and validated before processing.\"", "\"REAL-TIME PROCESSING\":\"Real-time processing is an approach where transactions are processed immediately as they occur, ensuring that information in the system is always up-to-date. However, it can be challenging to control, and the risk of errors is greater.\"", "\"ELECTRONIC POINT OF SALE (EPOS)\":Electronic Point of Sale (EPOS) is a computerized system used to record sales transactions. It utilizes bar code readers to capture details of each sale and can be linked to other systems for real-time data processing and inventory management. In a supermarket setting, the Transaction Processing System (TPS) may include an EPOS system, where goods are scanned by the cashier using a bar-code reader when the customer is checking out.", "\"ELECTRONIC DATA INTERCHANGE (EDI)\":Electronic Data Interchange (EDI) is a system that enables the supermarket's system to communicate with the suppliers' systems, facilitating transactions such as placing orders, receiving goods, and making payments.", "\"QUIZ ON INFORMATION SYSTEMS\":\"QUIZ ON INFORMATION SYSTEMS\" is a quiz that involves suggesting examples of information required from an information system for a market trader working in a fruit market and a materials purchasing department in a factory.", "\"TACTICAL LEVEL\":\"The tactical level of an organization involves short- to medium-term planning and decision-making by middle managers to implement strategies and achieve specific objectives.\"", "\"OPERATIONAL LEVEL\":\"The operational level of an organization involves day-to-day activities and decision-making by operational staff to ensure efficient and effective execution of tasks.\"", "\"INTERNAL INFORMATION\":\"Internal information refers to data generated within an organization, such as financial records, employee data, and internal reports.\"", "\"EXTERNAL INFORMATION\":\"External information refers to data obtained from outside an organization, such as market trends, competitor analysis, and regulatory requirements.\"", "\"CRITICAL SUCCESS FACTORS (CSFS)\":\"Critical Success Factors (CSFs) are the essential areas of activity that must be performed well for an organization to achieve its mission and objectives.\"", "\"DATA ANALYSIS TOOLS\":\"Data analysis tools are software applications and methodologies used to analyze data, identify patterns, and support decision-making processes.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}